In this press briefing, White House Press Secretary Robert Gibbs addresses the situation involving Shirley Sherrod, a former employee of the Department of Agriculture who was fired based on incomplete information. Gibbs explains that Secretary Vilsack is trying to reach Sherrod to apologize and discuss next steps. He emphasizes that many people, including those in the government and media, acted without all the facts. Gibbs states that everyone involved in the situation owes Sherrod an apology. He also discusses the signing of a financial reform bill and the ongoing economic challenges faced by the administration. Gibbs does not provide a specific answer regarding the President's involvement or whether Sherrod will be offered her job back.